===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|thurghfare}}, corresponding to {{compound|en|through|fare}}. Compare Old English {{m|ang|þurhfaran||to go through, go over, traverse, pierce, pass through, pass beyond, transcend, penetrate}}. Compare also {{cog|ang|þurhfær||inner secret place}}, {{cog|de|Durchfahrt||passage through, thoroughfare}}.

